# About
**Objective:** Become familiar with using Spark.ML to train a stacked ensemble of regressors
**File locations:** spark-labs/music_data.csv
**Successful outcome:** You will have trained and evaluated a stacked regression model
**Before you begin:**
**Related lessons:** Ensemble methods

---

paragraphs.title: Retrieve the music dataset
paragraphs.text:
%sh

rm -f /home/zeppelin/music_data.csv
wget -P /home/zeppelin https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/sci-241/music_data/music_data.csv
hdfs dfs -rm spark-labs/music_data.csv
hdfs dfs -put /home/zeppelin/music_data.csv spark-labs/

from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.tuning import CrossValidator
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.tuning import ParamGridBuilder

paragraphs.text:
%md
Make a parameter map to search over
~~~
params = ParamGridBuilder().addGrid(regressor.regParam,[0.001,0.01,0.1,1.0,10.0,100.0]).addGrid(regressor.elasticNetParam,[0.001,0.01,0.1,1.0]).addGrid(regressor.maxIter,[100,200,300,500,1000]).build()
~~~

paragraphs.title: 9 - Make a parameter map to search over

paragraphs.text:
%md
Set the CrossValidator object to use the specified regressor, evaluator, and parameter map over 10 folds
~~~
cv = CrossValidator(estimator=regressor, evaluator= evaluator, numFolds=10,estimatorParamMaps=params,parallelism = 4)
~~~
